#Text=The Prisoners of the Queen

#Text=Approaching the gateway of the Emerald City the travelers found it guarded by two girls of the Army of Revolt , who opposed their entrance by drawing the knitting-needles from their hair and threatening to prod the first that came near .
#Text=But the Tin Woodman was not afraid .

#Text= At this rate we will soon have your Majesty upon the throne again , " said the Tin Woodman , laughing at his easy conquest of the guards .

column1: #Text=" Thank you , friend Nick , " returned the Scarecrow , gratefully .
#Text=" Nothing can resist your kind heart and your sharp axe . "
#Text=As they passed the rows of houses they saw through the open doors that men were sweeping and dusting and washing dishes , while the women sat around in groups , gossiping and laughing .
#Text=" What has happened ? " the Scarecrow asked a sad-looking man with a bushy beard , who wore an apron and was wheeling a baby-carriage along the sidewalk .
#Text=" Why , we 've had a revolution , your Majesty as you ought to know very well , " replied the man ; " and since you went away the women have been running things to suit themselves .

column1: #Text=" Perhaps the women are made of castiron . "
#Text=No movement was made , as they passed along the street , to oppose their progress .
#Text=Several of the women stopped their gossip long enough to cast curious looks upon our friends , but immediately they would turn away with a laugh or a sneer and resume their chatter .

#Text=And when they met with several girls belonging to the Army of Revolt , those soldiers , instead of being alarmed or appearing surprised , merely stepped out of the way and allowed them to advance without protest .
#Text=This action rendered the Scarecrow uneasy .
#Text="

#Text= Nonsense ! " returned Nick Chopper , confidently ; " the silly creatures are conquered already ! "

column1: #Text=But the Scarecrow shook his head in a way that expressed doubt , and Tip said :
#Text=" It 's too easy , altogether .
#Text=Unopposed they reached the royal palace and marched up the marble steps , which had once been
#Text=172 Full page line-art drawing .
#Text=" IT'S TOO EASY , ALTOGETHER . "
#Text=173
#Text=thickly crusted with emeralds but were now filled with tiny holes where the jewels had been ruthlessly torn from their settings by the Army of Revolt .
#Text=And so far not a rebel barred their way .

#Text=Through the arched hallways and into the magnificent throne room marched the Tin Woodman and his followers , and here , when the green silken curtains fell behind them , they saw a curious sight .
#Text=Seated within the glittering throne was General Jinjur , with the Scarecrow 's second-best crown upon her head , and the royal sceptre in her right hand .
#Text=A box of caramels , from which she was eating , rested in her lap , and the girl seemed entirely at ease in her royal surroundings .
#Text=The Scarecrow stepped forward and confronted her , while the Tin Woodman leaned upon his axe and the others formed a half-circle back of his Majesty 's person .
#Text=" How dare you sit in my throne ? " demanded the Scarecrow , sternly eyeing the intruder .
#Text=" Do n't you know you are guilty of treason , and that there is a law against treason ? "
#Text=" The throne belongs to whoever is able to take it , " answered Jinjur , as she slowly ate another caramel .
#Text=" I have taken it , as you see ; so just now I am the Queen , and all who oppose me are guilty of
